context: "Timeline" is a loanword from English that has been adopted into Estonian. It refers to a chronological sequence or representation of events, showing when things happened in relation to each other. In Estonian usage, it typically maintains its English spelling and pronunciation but follows Estonian grammar rules for case endings when needed.
